Key Match Events: Coby White called out the Chicago Bulls' effort after their 143-107 loss to the Houston Rockets.
Houston Rockets forward Dillon Brooks drove to the basket against Chicago Bulls guards Coby White and Zach LaVine during the first half.
Post-Match Reflections: Coby White expressed that the team needs to compete at a higher level and be more physical.
White mentioned that giving up 140-plus points in back-to-back games is unacceptable and embarrassing.
He emphasized that it is a disservice to the organization and the fanbase.
